-------------------------------------------
what is iostream in C++
In C++, iostream is a core header file that stands for Input/Output Stream.
It is part of the C++ Standard Library and provides the basic functionality required to read data from an input (like a keyboard) and write data to an output (like a screen).
------------------------------
what is bits/stdc++.h>
#include <bits/stdc++.h> is a "catch-all" header file primarily used in competitive programming. 
It is not a standard C++ header; instead, it is a header provided by the GNU GCC compiler that includes nearly every standard library header in one line.
------------------------------------------
using namespace std means?
In C++, using namespace std; is a directive that tells the compiler to look into the Standard (std) Namespace for any names 
(functions, objects, or classes) it doesn't recognize.

----------------------------------
ADJ LIST in C++ 
#include <iostream>
#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
int main() {
    int n,m;
    cin >> n;
    cin >> m;
   vector<pair<int,int>> adj[n+1];
   for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
   {
       int u,v,wt;
       cin >> u >> v >> wt;
       adj[u].push_back({v,wt});
       adj[v].push_back({u,wt});
   }
    return 0;
}
